<subSubSection id="C331657B7061FFB0FEF9049D975CFA2C" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9436F07061FFB0FEF9049D902AFB14" blockId="1.[264,1325,972,1478]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FEF9049D9541FC0F" box="[264,366,972,997]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
. Recent publications on species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D737061FFB0FCE5049D9751FC0F" box="[788,894,972,997]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FCE5049D9751FC0F" box="[788,894,972,997]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Syscenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FC14049D90B1FC0C" author="Kensley" box="[997,1182,972,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Kensley, B. (2004) Redescription and distribution of two species of Syscenus (Crustacea, Isopoda, Aegidae) in the North Atlantic. Sarsia, 89 (3), 160 - 174." type="journal article" year="2004">
Kensley (
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FBA7049D90B9FC0C" box="[1110,1174,972,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FB5A049D9581FBE4" author="Kensley" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Kensley, B. &amp; Cartes, J. E. (2003) Records and distribution of Syscenus infelix in the deep Mediterranean (Crustacea: Isopoda: Aegidae. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 83 (4), 775 - 777." type="journal article" year="2003">
Kensley &amp; Cartes (
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FE9704A59589FBE4" box="[358,422,1012,1038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FE0304A596E4FBE4" box="[498,715,1012,1038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Ross, S. W., Sulak, K. J. &amp; Munroe, T. A. (2001) Association of Syscenus infelix (Crustacea: Isopoda: Aegidae) with benthopelagic rattail fishes, Nezumia spp. (Macrouridae), along the western North Atlantic continental slope. Marine Biology, 138 (3), 595 - 602." type="journal article">
Ross 
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FDC404A59644FBE7" box="[565,619,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FD7704A596ECFBE4" box="[646,707,1012,1038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on the parasitic habits of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D737061FFB0FBFD04A59569FBDC" authority="Harger, 1880" authorityName="Harger" authorityYear="1880" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infelix">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FBFD04A590E6FBE7" box="[1036,1225,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Syscenus infelix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FB2504A59569FBDC" author="Harger" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Harger, O. (1880) Report on the marine Isopoda of New England and adjacent waters. Report of the U. S. Commission for Fisheries, 6, 297 - 462." type="journal article" year="1880">
Harger, 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FEF9034D9569FBDC" box="[264,326,1052,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1880.0">1880</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FEA0034D95C1FBDC" author="Bruce" box="[337,494,1052,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Bruce, N. L. (1997) A new species of Syscenus Harger, 1880 (Crustacea: Isopoda: Aegidae) from eastern Australia with a revised diagnosis to the genus. Records of the Australian Museum, 49, 113 - 120." type="journal article" year="1997">
Bruce (
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FE56034D95CBFBDC" box="[423,484,1052,1078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a revised generic diagnosis. The genus can be recognized by the pleon being abruptly narrower than the pereon, lamellar uropods and maxilliped palp with three articles; all but two species entirely lack eyes. The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D737061FFB0FB5B033D95ECFB44" authority="Tattersall, 1909" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1909" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Xenuraega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FB5B033D9104FB6F" box="[1194,1323,1132,1157]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Xenuraega</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FEF903C595ECFB44" author="Tattersall" box="[264,451,1172,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Tattersall, W. M. (1909) II. Amphipoda and Isopoda, with descriptions of two new species. Memoirs of the Challenger Society, 1, 210 - 219." type="journal article" year="1909">
Tattersall, 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FE7703C595ECFB44" box="[390,451,1172,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1909.0">1909</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also with a narrow pleon, is immediately distinguished by the uropodal rami, with a short and stub­like endopod and an exceptionally elongate, filamentous exopod with numerous plumose setae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FD2003B597D9FB14" author="Bruce" box="[721,1014,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Bruce, N. L. (1993) Redescription of the overlooked crustacean isopod genus Xenuraega (Aegidae, Flabellifera). Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 73, 617 - 625." type="journal article" year="1993">
Bruce 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FCD103B59772FB14" box="[800,861,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1993.0">1993</number>
, figs 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FC6C03B59783FB14" box="[925,940,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FC1403B597D9FB14" box="[997,1014,1252,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9436F07061FFB0FEC9025D975CFA2C" blockId="1.[264,1325,972,1478]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
Most species of the genus lack any trace of eyes or ommatidia. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D737061FFB0FBB8025D9613FAA4" authority="Menzies &amp; George, 1972" authorityName="Menzies &amp; George" authorityYear="1972" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruanus">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FBB8025D9105FACF" box="[1097,1322,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Syscenus peruanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B017061FFB0FEF902659613FAA4" author="Menzies" box="[264,572,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Menzies, R. J. &amp; George, R. Y. (1972) Isopod Crustacea of the Peru - Chile Trench. Anton Bruun Report. Scientific Results of the Southeast Pacific Expedition, Texas A &amp; M Press: College Station Texas, 9, 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="1972">
Menzies &amp; George, 
<number id="3DE324D77061FFB0FE0F02659613FAA4" box="[510,572,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the only previously described species known to have eyes, is known from a single juvenile specimen, atypically deep for the genus at 
<quantity id="4CD39B157061FFB0FB8F020D9108FA9C" box="[1150,1319,1372,1398]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5675" metricValueMax="4.609" metricValueMin="4.526" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="4567.5" valueMax="4609.0" valueMin="4526.0">4526–4609 m</quantity>
, from off 
<collectingCountry id="F33C76607061FFB0FE8302D59583FA74" box="[370,428,1412,1438]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D737061FFB0FE4602D59670FA77" box="[439,607,1412,1437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Syscenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAE27061FFB0FE4602D59670FA77" box="[439,607,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Syscenus karu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57997061FFB0FD9702D596EEFA74" box="[614,705,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has distinct eyes, and the lack of eyes can no longer be considered a generic character state for the genus.
</paragraph>
